\section*{Simplify Expressions with Absolute Value}

A negative number is a number less than 0 . The negative numbers are to the left of zero on the number line. See Figure 1.2.

\begin{figure}
\includegraphics[alt={},max width=\textwidth]{./images/fc686fde-1413-455c-8a02-0a26b98e7fc3-0036_186_657_2154_734.jpg}
