$$\begin{aligned}
& -\frac{315}{770} \\
& -\frac{3 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 7}{2 \cdot 5 \cdot 7 \cdot 11}
\end{aligned}$$

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|}
\hline Step 2. Simplify using the equivalent fractions property by dividing out common factors. & \begin{tabular}{l}
Mark the common factors 5 and 7. \\
Divide out the common factors
\end{tabular} & $$\begin{aligned}
& -\frac{3 \cdot 3 \cdot 8 \cdot 7}{2 \cdot 8 \cdot 7 \cdot 11} \\
& -\frac{3 \cdot 3}{2 \cdot 11}
\end{aligned}$$ \\
\hline Step 3. Multiply the remaining factors, if necessary. & & $-\frac{9}{22}$ \\
