\section*{Add and Subtract Decimals}

To add or subtract decimals, we line up the decimal points. By lining up the decimal points this way, we can add or subtract the corresponding place values. We then add or subtract the numbers as if they were whole numbers and then place the decimal point in the sum.

\section*{HOW TO}

Add or subtract decimals.
Step 1. Determine the sign of the sum or difference.
Step 2. Write the numbers so the decimal points line up vertically.
Step 3. Use zeros as placeholders, as needed.
Step 4. Add or subtract the numbers as if they were whole numbers. Then place the decimal point in the answer under the decimal points in the given numbers.
Step 5. Write the sum or difference with the appropriate sign.

\section*{EXAMPLE 1.35}

Add or subtract: (a) $-23.5-41.38$ (b) $14.65-20$.

\section*{Solution}
(a)

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline & -23.5-41.38 \\
\hline The difference will be negative. To subtract, we add the numerals. Write the numbers so the decimal points line up vertically. & 23.5 $\underline{+41.38}$ \\
\hline Put 0 as a placeholder after the 5 in 23.5. & 23.50 \\
\hline Remember, $\frac{5}{10}=\frac{50}{100}$ so $0.5=0.50$. & $\underline{+41.38}$ \\
\hline \multirow{3}{*}{\begin{tabular}{l}
Add the numbers as if they were whole numbers. \\
Then place the decimal point in the sum.
\end{tabular}} & 23.50 \\
\hline & $\underline{+41.38}$ \\
\hline & 64.88 \\
\hline Write the result with the correct sign. & $-23.5-41.38=-64.88$ \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
(b)
$\_\_\_\_$
14.65-20

The difference will be negative. To subtract, we subtract 14.65 from 20.

\begin{tabular}{ll}
\hline Write the numbers so the decimal points line up vertically. & 20 \\
$\underline{-14.65}$ \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

Remember, 20 is a whole number, so place the decimal point after the 0 .

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|}
\hline \multirow{2}{*}{Put in zeros to the right as placeholders.} & \multicolumn{2}{|c|}{20.00} \\
\hline & \multicolumn{2}{|l|}{$\underline{-14.65}$} \\
\hline \multirow{5}{*}{Subtract and place the decimal point in the answer.} & \multicolumn{2}{|c|}{99} \\
\hline & 1 & 10 \\
\hline & 2 & 0 \\
\hline & -1 & 6 \\
\hline & 5 & 3 \\
\hline Write the result with the correct sign. & \multicolumn{2}{|l|}{$14.65-20=-5.35$} \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
