4.075 \\
$\times 3.9$
\end{tabular} \\
\hline Multiply. & \begin{tabular}{l}
4.075 \\
$\times 3.9$ \\
36675 \\
12225 \\
158925
\end{tabular} \\
\hline \begin{tabular}{l}
Add the number of decimal places in the factors $(1+3)$. \\
Place the decimal point 4 places from the right.
\end{tabular} & \begin{tabular}{l}
4.075 \\
$\times 3.9$ \\
36675 \\
12225 \\
15.8925 \\
4 places
\end{tabular} \\
\hline The signs are the different, so the product is negative. & $(-3.9)(4.075)=-15.8925$ \\
